crops.institution_involved: Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria
crops.description: Plants of a cold-resistant variety collected at nearly 6,000 feet altitude in the high country around Johannesburg. Seeds and plants presented by I. B. Pole Evans, Chief, Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria.

crops.institution_involved: Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria
crops.description: Plants collected near Vereening, at nearly 3,000 feet altitude. Seeds and plants presented by I. B. Pole Evans, Chief, Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria.

crops.institution_involved: Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria
crops.description: Seed from the Rietondale Pasture Station, Pretoria. Seeds and plants presented by I. B. Pole Evans, Chief, Division of Plant Industry, Department of Agriculture, Pretoria.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A stout bush a foot or more high, with linear-filiform leaves one-half to 1 1/2 inches long and numerous small yellow flower heads on slender stems an inch long. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: Members of this genus are small, rigid, shrubby plants with yellow flower heads. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A rigid twiggy shrub with long erect branches and trifid leaves an inch or more long with linear lobes. The yellow flower heads are half an inch across. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A rigid, much-branched shrub, 1 to 2 feet high, with thinly silky tufted linear leaves up to an inch long and chrysanthemumlike flowers having reddish or yellow disk flowers and white rays. It is said to be a valuable pasture plant for sheep. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists. For previous introduction see 93291.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A dwarf shrub 1 to 3 feet high, with very small ovate or triangular, spirally arranged leaves and inconspicuous flowers. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A much-branched, semishrubby perennial with fleshy leaves less than 1 inch long, varying from linear to ovate-oblong. The small inconspicuous flowers are borne in leafy racemes and are followed by 3- to 4-winged nutlike fruits. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists. For previous introduction see 91238.

crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape
crops.description: A bushy shrub 1 to 3 feet high, with alternate linear leaves, entire or 3- toothed, and numerous small flower heads. Seeds presented by Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg Cape. A collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists.

Cuttings presented by James C. Scarffe, San Pedro de Macoris. Porvenir-30. An erect vigorous variety which becomes 7 to 9 feet high. It matures in 5 months, is fairly drought resistant, and has never been seen with mosaic. Introduced for the use of Department specialists working with sugarcane.
